# All variables here are OPTIONAL. Harness boots with sensible defaults.
# `make setup` generates a `.env.local` with a real HARNESS_TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY
# the first time you run it.
#
# GitHub credentials, OpenAI API key, and ChatGPT/Codex tokens are NOT stored
# here — they live encrypted in `data/harness.db` after you walk through the
# Settings dialog (gear icon, top-right).

# 32-byte base64 key that encrypts secrets at rest in SQLite (OAuth tokens,
# OpenAI API key). If unset, a deterministic dev key is used — fine for
# local hacking, but anything you save with the dev key can be decrypted by
# anyone who clones the project. `make setup` generates a real one.
#   openssl rand -base64 32
HARNESS_TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY=

# --- Storage paths (optional overrides) -------------------------------------
# Local file path for the SQLite DB.
# HARNESS_DB_PATH=./data/harness.db
# Remote libsql / Turso URL — overrides HARNESS_DB_PATH.
# HARNESS_DB_URL=libsql://your-db.turso.io
# HARNESS_DB_AUTH_TOKEN=

# Where cloned repos live and where we materialise codex's auth.json.
# HARNESS_REPOS_DIR=./data/repos
# HARNESS_CODEX_HOME=./data/codex-home

# --- External binaries (optional) -------------------------------------------
# Path to the cocoindex-code CLI. Defaults to $HOME/.local/bin/ccc.
# CCC_BIN=
